nated by the Spanish since the voyages of Christopher Columbus in the late 15th century. Lewis and Clark set off Today is the anniversary of the first step in a long journey. On May 14, 1804, Meriwether Lewis and William Clark embarked on their famous expedition to the Pacific coast of North America. Over the duration of the trip, which lasted until September 23, 1806, from St. Louis , Missouri, to the Pacific Ocean and back, the Corps of Discovery, as the expedition company was called, traveled nearly 8,000 miles (13,000 km). Israel founded On this day in 1948just before the expiry of the British mandate in Palestine  David Ben-Gurion and the Jewish Peoples Council proclaimed the establishment of the State of Israel . The next day, the first Arab-Israeli war formally began , although it followed a civil war that began after the United Nations passed a partition plan on November 29, 1947. For Israel, the war is remembered as the War of Independence. For Arabs, it is remembered as the Nakba (from Arabic, meaning Catastrophe). Popular on Britannica Articles Qatar Leo XIV list of state capitals in the United States Florence Nightingale Donner party Balochistan Buddha American Idol winners Leo XIII Our Lady of Ftima Show More Show Less Features Did Marie-Antoinette Really Say Let Them Eat Cake? What Is the Emoluments Clause? Timeline of the 1990s What Is the Most Widely Practiced Religion in the World? Cruel and Unusual Punishments: 15 Types of Torture Cinco de Mayo Timeline of the 2000s Cannibalism: Cultures, Cures, Cuisine, and Calories Whats the Difference Between Bison and Buffalo? 7 of the Worlds Deadliest Plants Show More Show Less Lists Flags That Look Alike New Seven Wonders of the World Spies Like Us: 10 Famous Names in the Espionage Game 7 Deadliest Weapons in History Timeline of the American Civil Rights Movement Weapons of World War I 11 of the Worlds Most Famous Warplanes 6 Animals That Eat Their Mates The 6 Deadliest Earthquakes Since 1950 Korean War Timel